Key Match Events: Rohit Sharma scored 92 runs, including 76 off 52 balls in boundaries.
Josh Hazlewood took 1 wicket for 14 runs with 14 balls on a length.
Travis Head scored 76 runs, but could not prevent the loss.
Axar Patel took a sensational catch to dismiss David Warner for 6 runs.
Post-Match Reflections: Rohit Sharma's performance was crucial in leading India to the semi-finals.
India's spinners, especially Kuldeep Yadav and Axar Patel, played key roles in restricting Australia's run chase.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rohit Sharma's boundary rate was 71 runs out of 24 invitations to play front-foot shots.
Travis Head's innings was his 11th in T20Is, but India's spinners managed to restrict his effectiveness.
